name: Chase Nelson
text:
Frontier is a decent airline with cheap fares. The airport is convenient but really small. It’s embarrassing for travelers to see a facility that doesn’t even have proper  tarmac, gangway, or an actual baggage carousel .  Literally people carry them off the plane onto a dolly and set them out in the main lobby/entrance area by staff members (untrained teenagers) and then just let all the people crowded around to cipher through all the bags to find your own luggage.
I can’t imagine this becoming the main airport for Mobile or it even being considered a international airport or hub. Very scary, but leave it to that $ pocketing mayor and old Mobilians..

text: Lies,Lies and more Lies the maintenance man tried to tell my husband that if he was to use the GFI outlet on the pole above were we plugged our camper in it would drive our bill out of site because he didn't want to replace it. We explained  to management before moving in our camper was an older model that needed work and was told no problem. My husband an honorably discharged veteran was then the harassing began because he told management he was no idiot and the GFI needed fixing. The bully maintenance then made our life miserable and even cut off the power to our camper. Now we are once again homeless until the lawyers handle this. Do Not Ever Rent From These Crooks. They have slandered our names and picked on us because of the age of our camper and my being on dissability while my husband waits on his veterans benefits.
